  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\nIf I turn of the \"Automatic Selection\" switch in mailserver settings, only a the list of mailservers scroll. The other elements stay fixed. This makes it hard to check the available mailservers (video attached): \n\nhttps://imgur.com/frFqUWM\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nThe entire screen should scroll making it easier to access and select mailservers.\n\n#### Actual behavior\nOnly the mailserver list scrolls, the other elements stay fixed.\n\n#### Notes\n\nI built this feature earlier in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/11191\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\nRules for the future PR to be accepted.\n\n### Reproduction\n1. Open status app\n2. Goto Settings > Sync Settings > Mailservers\n3. Turn off \"Automatic Selection\"\n4. Only the list of mailservers will scroll (see attached video)\n\n\n### Additional Information\n\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n- Status version: 1.8\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
